$ curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/ai/route   -H "content-type: application/json"   -d '{"q":"How can I reduce p95 latency?"}'
{"answer":"Consider optimizing your code, improving server resources, and using load balancing."}

$ curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8080/ai/route   -H "content-type: application/json"   -d '{"q":"Place a hold on invoice INV-1001 for $120.50"}'
{"action":"createPaymentHold","args":{"invoiceId":"INV-1001","amount":120.5}}

>>> The Flow <<<
1).curl sends JSON → Spring parses it.
2).Controller builds prompt + options → passes to OpenAI via Spring AI.
3).OpenAI returns JSON (thanks to responseFormat).
4).JSON is mapped into RouterResult → post-processed → returned as JSON.

>>> K6 <<<
 $env:BASE_URL = "http://localhost:8080"
 PS C:\demoActual> k6 run .\src\main\perf\k6-light.js